# This file is used to hold the list of all 3rd party PPAs in the following format.
# ProgramName   	      	       	    ActualProgramName					PPA			TypeOfInstall					Properties			
# (the programname for our reference) (the actual programnamname that is used to install)	(the actual PPA)	(is it a basic, desktop or dev software)	1:1 (indicating dependency and script)
# Comments	       	   	   
# URLs for further info. (URLs only)
#
# Use ! to fill an empty column as a place holder. Do NOT leave empty columns.
#
# Property fields detail
# ----------------------
# The first flag indicates that there is a separate script available for installing and or configuring this software, in which case that should be run.
# The second flag indicates whether it is a dependency installation or a standalone installation. Any dependency PPA follows the main PPA where the properties column has the dependency property set to 1 which is the second flag.
# The third flag indicates a message for TODO should be recorded after installation.
# The fourth flag indicates it is a 'dist-upgrade' instead of a typical installation. This option is used when a defult installation is to be upgraded after a PPA is added.
#
# Most software installations are stright forward and only require the installation of the software provided by the PPA. However, others might require some other dependencies, in which case those should be installed first before installing the actual PPA.

#ProgramName   	     	    ActualProgramName     	  PPA					TypeOfInstall	Properties	Comments
